The paper deals with the characterization of the generalized degrees of freedom (GDoF) of a multiple input multiple output (MIMO) interference channel (IC) with partial channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT). This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also uses the aligned image sets approach, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of the channel, which can be considered as a topic in computer engineering (cs.CE).
